COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 11:15AM PT today, over 1.5 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 26.9 thousand have died.

In the last day, 1.3 thousand new infections were reported and 1 deaths. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 52.8 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 83.3% have their 1st shot and 75.2% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 10.7 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~98 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Dec-25 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
